        <mxCell id="4nCGfrJDZ0LfG-0GbpCk-1" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;" value="&lt;div align=&quot;left&quot;&gt;Deliver a report (1 A4 page, max. 500 words) showing the detected objects, their positions&amp;nbsp;relative to the starting point, and the optimal recovery route. For distance measurements, use as reference the center of gravity of each object’s projected surface on the ground. For the theoretical recovery, the rover would require a circular clearance area with a diameter of 1 m to navigate between obstacles. The rover could use the whole Arena (10 m x 10 m) for maneuvering. The rover would start at the drone’s starting point and must return there after recovery.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=&quot;left&quot;&gt;No text is required, only a map including:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=&quot;left&quot;&gt;- the path&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=&quot;left&quot;&gt;- obstacles and probes&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=&quot;left&quot;&gt;and a table listing:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=&quot;left&quot;&gt;- each detected object&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=&quot;left&quot;&gt;- a picture of it and its position&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
